Package com.ibm.streams.management.domain

Interface DomainMXBean

public interface DomainMXBean
DomainMXBean provides attributes, operations, and notifications for managing a Streams domain.

ObjectNameBuilder.domain(String) can be used to build the ObjectName for a DomainMXBean.

Notifications:
A DomainMXBean supports sending the following notifications:

javax.management.AttributeChangeNotification.ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE
Only a subset of the attributes support attribute change notification. A note is included in the attribute description for each attribute that supports attribute change notification

Notifications.DOMAIN_TRUSTED_ORIGIN_ADDED
Notifications.DOMAIN_TRUSTED_ORIGIN_REMOVED
Notifications.INSTANCE_CREATED
Notifications.INSTANCE_DELETED
Notifications.LOG_ERROR
Notifications.LOG_WARNING
Notifications.RESOURCE_ADDED
Notifications.RESOURCE_CHANGED
Notifications.RESOURCE_REMOVED
Notifications.RESOURCE_TAG_ADDED
Notifications.RESOURCE_TAG_CHANGED
Notifications.RESOURCE_TAG_REMOVED
Notifications.SECURITY_ROLE_CREATED
Notifications.SECURITY_ROLE_DELETED

Notification categories:
These categories can be used with notification filters to easily filter out all notifications in a category.
Notifications.DOMAIN_NOTIFICATION
Notifications.INSTANCE_NOTIFICATION
Notifications.LOG_NOTIFICATION
Notifications.RESOURCE_NOTIFICATION
Notifications.SECURITY_NOTIFICATION

    • createOperationListener

      ObjectName createOperationListener()
      Creates an OperationListenerMXBean for tracking status messages associated with operations invoked on this bean. Once the operation listener is created, the listener Id can be passed as a parameter on operations which support it. An operation listener can be reused for multiple operation invocations; however, the behavior is undefined if it is used for concurrent operations. All existing messages are cleared at the start of each operation for which the listener is used. The unregister operation should be called on the operation listener after the listener is no longer needed to free the associated memory. All operation listeners are automatically unregistered when the monitored bean is unregistered. An operation listener is also automatically unregistered if it has had no activity for a certain amount of time. The inactivity time is controlled by the JMX_INACTIVITY_TIMEOUT property and is set to 30 minutes by default. If an operation listener bean is needed again, a new one can be created.
      Returns:
      the object name of the created listener bean.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the operation is unable to complete successfully.

    • setProperty

      void setProperty(DomainMXBean.PropertyId id, String value)
      Updates the value of a configuration property. Changes to some property values do not occur immediately after being updated; rather the change is pending the restart of the domain. To determine which property changes require a domain restart see the DomainMXBean.PropertyId value descriptions. For properties which have an enumeration for possible values, the toString() method on the enumeration value must be used for the value parameter on this call.
      Parameters:
      id - identifies the property for which the value is changed.
      value - specifies the new property value.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the operation is unable to complete successfully.
      NullPointerException - if id is null.
      SecurityException - if the current user does not have the required permissions to perform the operation. Information about Streams permissions can be found in the product documentation. See topic: Security objects for Teracloud Streams domains and instances.

    • setRestrictedConfiguration

      void setRestrictedConfiguration(String name, String value)
      Creates a new restricted configuration or updates the value of an existing one. A restricted configuration is a way to store sensitive configuration information associated with the domain. The restricted configuration value is stored encrypted to protect the sensitive information. Only domain administrators are able to work with restricted configurations.
      Parameters:
      name - identifies the name of the restricted configuration to create or update.
      value - specifies the value to store for the restricted configuration.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the operation is unable to complete successfully.
      NullPointerException - if name or value is null.
      IllegalArgumentException - if name is blank.
      SecurityException - if the current user does not have the required permissions to perform the operation. Information about Streams permissions can be found in the product documentation. See topic: Security objects for Teracloud Streams domains and instances.
